          "meta": Map {},
          "uri": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "<div xmlns=\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\\"><p>I work in AWS√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s Serverless group, and in the process of pulling together my<a href=\\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IPOvrK3S3gQ\\">presentation at re:Invent</a>, discovered that I have a lot of opinions on the
subject and, while they may well be wrong, are at least well-informed.  You can watch that YouTube, but who√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s got an hour to spare?
And anyhow, blogging√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s really my favorite medium, so here we go.  If I tried to glom them all together into one mega-essay it√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢d be
brutally long, so let√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s go short-form.</p><h2 id=\\"p-3\\">The Serverless Fragments</h2><p>√¢‚Ç¨≈ìServerless Fragment√¢‚Ç¨¬ù has five syllables and<span class=\\"o\\">ongoing</span>doesn√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢t have that much room at the top of the page
for the title, so let√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s say √¢‚Ç¨≈ìSF√¢‚Ç¨¬ù.</p><ol><li><p><a href=\\"/ongoing/When/201x/2018/12/10/SF-1\\">SF 1: What is serverless?</a>Tl;dr: It√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s when you don√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢t have to reserve capacity before you start.  But it√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s not a binary
condition.</p></li><li><p><a href=\\"/ongoing/When/201x/2018/12/10/SF-2\\">SF 2: Why serverless?</a>Tl;dr: Frugality, Security, Elasticity.  That part√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s a no-brainer, but will you also get better
software?</p></li><li><p><a href=\\"/ongoing/When/201x/2018/12/11/SF-3\\">SF 3: Serverless everything?</a>Tl;dr: Nope, serverless where possible. To start with, think about control planes and data
planes.</p></li><li><p><a href=\\"/ongoing/When/201x/2018/12/14/SF-4\\">SF 4: Serverless latency?</a>Tl;dr: It√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s complicated. And, there are things to do about it.</p></li><li><p><a href=\\"/ongoing/When/201x/2018/12/30/SF-5\\">SF 5: Serverless bills?</a>Tl;dr: Not<em>always</em>lower. But it depends how you count it.</p></li></ol></div>",
