          "uri": "http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom",
          "value": "<div xmlns=\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\\">Sometimes we fans get a little over-excited and declaim that<em>everything</em>should be serverless. After all, we√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢re pretty convinced that owning data centers and computers is becoming a thing of the past.  Well then, how could configuring your own hosts and paying for them even when they√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢re not working ever be a good idea?  Let√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s try to be moderate and pragmatic:<em>Serverless, where possible</em>.</div>",
