          "value": "<div xmlns=\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\\">More or less all the big APIs are RESTful these days.  Yeah, you can quibble about what √¢‚Ç¨≈ìREST√¢‚Ç¨¬ù means (and I will, a bit) but the assertion is broadly true.  Is it going to stay that way forever?  Seems unlikely.  So, what√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s next?</div>",
