heading out in any direction you damn well please, as far as the road goes.  Making that possible really just can√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢t be a bad thing.</p><h2 id=\\"p-2\\">But√¢‚Ç¨¬¶</h2><p>Automobiles have had to be regulated fiercely almost from day one: Their speeds, where they can drive and park,
the safety standards on their tires and electronics and brakes and crumple zones and seatbelts and child seating, and of course
